\label{tab:split}
\begin{tabular}{l r l}
\toprule
\textbf{Split} & \textbf{Count} & \textbf{Purpose} \\
\midrule
Training & 8,829 (70\%) & Model training \\
Validation & 1,892 (15\%) & Early stopping \& LR scheduling \\
Test & 1,893 (15\%) & Final reported metrics \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Data Challenges}

Several challenges make this dataset difficult:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Pixel-level class imbalance:} Most pixels in tampered images are still authentic. The tampered region is often very small.
    \item \textbf{Forgery type imbalance:} Copy-move forgeries (3,295) significantly outnumber splicing forgeries (1,828).
    \item \textbf{Compression artifacts:} JPEG artifacts can act as shortcuts, leading to data leakage if not handled carefully.
\end{itemize}


