\subsection{Model Architecture}

The model is a \textbf{UNet}~\cite{ronneberger2015unet} encoder-decoder segmentation network, implemented using the Segmentation Models PyTorch (SMP) library~\cite{yakubovskiy2019smp}.

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Encoder:} ResNet-34~\cite{he2016resnet} pretrained on ImageNet. All convolutional weights are \textit{frozen}; only BatchNorm layers are set to training mode (unfrozen). This allows the normalization statistics to adapt from natural images to ELA forensic images, while keeping the learned feature hierarchies intact. The first convolutional layer is adapted to accept 9 input channels.
    \item \textbf{Decoder:} 5 upsampling blocks with channel dimensions (256, 128, 64, 32, 16) and skip connections at 4 resolution levels. Optional CBAM attention modules are placed after each decoder block.
    \item \textbf{Output:} A single-channel sigmoid activation producing a 384$\times$384 pixel probability map. A threshold of 0.5 converts this to a binary mask.
    \item \textbf{Image-level classification:} Derived from the segmentation output --- if any pixel in the predicted mask exceeds the threshold, the image is classified as tampered.
\end{itemize}

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{Model Parameter Summary}
\label{tab:params}
\begin{tabular}{l r}
\toprule
\textbf{Component} & \textbf{Parameters} \\
\midrule
Total parameters & 24.4M \\
Trainable parameters & 3.17M (13\%) \\
Encoder (frozen convolutions) & 21.3M \\
Decoder (trainable) & $\sim$3.17M \\
CBAM attention (optional) & +11,402 (+0.36\%) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}


\subsection{CBAM Attention Module}

CBAM (Convolutional Block Attention Module)~\cite{woo2018cbam} is injected into all 5 UNet decoder blocks. It applies two sequential attention operations:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Channel attention:} Learns \textit{which feature channels} are most relevant. Uses a shared MLP (with bottleneck ratio 16) on both average-pooled and max-pooled features, combined with sigmoid gating.
    \item \textbf{Spatial attention:} Learns \textit{which spatial locations} to focus on. Concatenates channel-wise average and max pooling, processes with a 7$\times$7 convolution, and applies sigmoid.
\end{enumerate}

CBAM adds only 11,402 parameters (0.36\% of trainable parameters) but produced a +3.57 percentage point improvement in Pixel~F1 --- the highest improvement-per-parameter of any change tested.


